**Three-Cup Squid**

Ingredients:
12 oz cleaned squid, cut into pieces
6 slices peeled ginger
6 cloves garlic (skin peeled)
2 tablespoons sesame oil
1 1/2 tablespoon soy sauce
1 1/2 tablespoon Shaoxing wine or Chinese rice wine
1 1/2 tablespoon dark sweet soy sauce
      
     How to make a delicious Taiwanese food of Three-Cup Squid? First Clean the squid and cut into pieces, rinse with cold water. Then heat up a pot of water and bring it to boil. Just put the squid in boiling water for about 20 seconds. Drain and set aside.
Next, heat up a pan to high heat and add some oil. Stir-fry 6 slices peeled garlic and ginger until you can smell them. Then add 1 1/2 tablespoon sweet soy sauce and Shaoxing wine. In the end, add the squid and stir. Now you have a tasty dishes.


